1:46 PM Defendant Jed James Flannery appeared by video, in custody. Attorney Peter Kruger in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case. Address verified.  Victim wants defendant to come back home. State is requesting no contact with address. Attorney Craker making special appearance, receives complaint, waives reading. Enters not guilty pleas to counts 4 and 5, requests preliminary hearing. Court accepts pleas.  State requests $20,000 cash, no contact with Victim 1 and do not return to address in Bennett, WI. Cites priors strangulation and battery cases. Cites additional felony cases. state requests no contact with Victim at all, victim wants to have some sort of contact but not in person. State opposes this. May return one time with law enforcement to retrieve personal property.
Court questions contact requests. Is she living at address or not. Victim may or may not be living at the address. 
Craker agrees with court's logic on no contact. if she moves out he could move back into the home which he owns.  Douglas county resident most of his life. has made all appearances in his other matters. Not much money to post. 
Defendant indicates he could 3,000 or 4,000.
Court orders $10,000 cash, with conditions of no contact with Victim 1. No use or possession of dangerous weapon. not ordering no contact with residence but if she still lives there he cannot return to residence. if victim remains in home, may return one time with law enforcement to retrieve personal property.
